reviewText: Excellent example of, The Living Theatre, of 1968-1970. The Pacifistic Anarchy of, The Living Theatre, was a collective effort of the Living Theatre Company as a whole and truly reflects the creative talents involved and their unique approach to political, social and economic problems of society.
I am absolutely thrilled by this rare and brilliant record of revolutionary 1960s theatre! It arrived in perfect condition - complete and 'good as new'.
I like it! It was really awesome piece of experimental avant garde theatre from the Living Theatre. It worths every penny
